This used to be one of my favorite breakfast cereals, until I learned about GMOs (genetically modified organisms).  Honey Nut Cheerios contains "modified corn" as the second ingredient, and since they do not specify "organic" or "non-GMO", and corn is one of the most genetically modified crops in our country, there is a high probability this cereal contains GMOs.  We typically only trust companies who specify on the packaging that they source non-gmo ingredients or have a company statement that they do not use GMOs, such as Barbara's Bakery and Annie's.  Amazon has an incredible selection of organic and/or non-GMO cereals and breakfast products!  [...]
